devdoc.author: Adil Mezghouti

params._benefitor: the address of the person who will be the recipient of the deposited funds
params._bucket: the name of the bucket in which the funds will be deposited

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._fromBucket: the bucket to which the funds are associated

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Allows families to deposit, lock, unlock, and release funds for the benefits of their children.

addFunds(address,string).notice: Adds funds to the smart contract and associate them to a specific bucketNote that the funds will be assigned logically through buckets and will not be effectively owned by the benefitor until the admin/owner releases the funds to her

releaseFunds(address,string).notice: Moves the amount associated with a specific bucket to the provided address
